    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-11-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-11-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="85"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d85">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Townsend</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-11-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 17, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The President directs you to convey, through the appropriate channel, his
                    sympathy with His Majesty by reason of the attempt upon <pb facs="0180" n="100"
                        xml:id="pg_100"/> his life, and sincere congratulations in his own name and
                    in the name of the people of the United States that the King has been
                    providentially saved from harm and the Belgian people from affliction.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
